revision.text:
{{Infobox magazine | title = Brooklyn Magazine | circulation = 25,000 | founder = [[Daniel Stedman]], Scott Stedman | founded = 2010 | firstdate = Spring 2011 | frequency = Monthly | company = Northside Media Group | country = USA | based = Brooklyn | language = English | website = {{URL|bkmag.com}} | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Brooklyn Magazine''''' is an [[United States|American]] glossy quarterly celebrating the arts, fashion, and high-end culture of [[Brooklyn]], [[New York City|New York]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/05/fashion/magazines-about-brooklyn-life-abound-noticed.html?_r=1|title=Brooklyn Life Abound Noticed|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref>
==History== ''Brooklyn Magazine'' was founded by Northside Media Group (brothers Scott and [[Daniel Stedman]], the same team behind the popular free alt-weekly ''[[L Magazine]]''. Its editor-in-chief is Mike Conklin<ref>{{cite web|last=Stoeffel |first=Kat |url=http://observer.com/2011/03/new-yorker-writers-are-brooklyn-writers-too-the-selfloathing-gentrifier-and-friends-launch-borough-glossy/ |title='New Yorker' Writers Are 'Brooklyn' Writers Too! The Self-Loathing Gentrifier and Friends Launch Borough Glossy |publisher=Observer |date= |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> and it shares most of its staff with ''The L''.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.vocus.com/invocus/media-moves/magazine/regional-magazine-for-brooklyn-dwellers-launched-this-week/ |title=Regional magazine for Brooklyn dwellers launched this week - inVocus Media Blog |publisher=Vocus.com |date=2011-03-18 |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> Its first issue landed in the Spring of 2011. In June 2012, Northside Media Group re-launched the magazine's website. In addition to what has appeared in print, BKmag.com features web-only content, including blogs for Food and Style and ''Brooklyn Abridged'', a comprehensive news feed for the borough. In September 2012 the website launched a special online-only issue dedicated to Brooklyn literature to coincide with the Brooklyn Book Festival.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bkmag.com/brooklyn/the-essential-guide-to-brooklyn-literature-in-2012/Content?oid=2262927 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922035623/http://www.bkmag.com/brooklyn/the-essential-guide-to-brooklyn-literature-in-2012/Content?oid=2262927 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-09-22 |title=The Essential Guide to Brooklyn Literature in 2012 &#124; Features &#124; Brooklyn Magazine |publisher=Bkmag.com |date=2012-09-20 |accessdate=2013-08-17 }}</ref>
==Covers== ''Brooklyn Magazine''{{'}}s first cover star was ''[[Boardwalk Empire]]''{{'}}s [[Michael Pitt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://b612-austin.blogspot.com/2011/03/michael-pitt-for-brooklyn-magazine.html |title=a forgotten asteroid: michael pitt for brooklyn magazine |publisher=B612-austin.blogspot.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> Subsequent covers have featured other Brooklynites of note, such as [[Emily Mortimer]],<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://portroids.blogspot.com/2011/07/portroid-in-brooklyn-magazine.html |title=Portroids: Portroid in Brooklyn Magazine! |publisher=Portroids.blogspot.com |date=2011-07-11 |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> [[David Cross]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://swipelife.com/2012/04/04/david-cross-interview-with-brooklyn-magazine/ |title=David Cross Interview with Brooklyn Magazine |publisher=SwipeLife |date=2012-04-04 |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> and [[Olivia Thirlby]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://swipelife.com/2012/01/05/olivia-thirlby-interview-for-brooklyn-magazine/ |title=Olivia Thirlby Interview for Brooklyn Magazine |publisher=SwipeLife |date=2012-01-05 |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref>
