{{Nihongo|'''''Heavy Object'''''|ヘヴィーオブジェクト|Hevī Obujekuto}} is a Japanese [[light novel]] series, written by [[Kazuma Kamachi]] and illustrated by Ryō Nagi. [[ASCII Media Works]] have published fourteen volumes since 2009 under their [[Dengeki Bunko]] label. It has received three [[manga]] adaptations. A 24-episode [[anime]] television series adaptation produced by [[J.C.Staff]] (with 3DCG provided by [[Sanzigen]]) aired from October 2 to March 25, 2016.<ref name="Staff"/>

==Plot==
In the future, the development of massive war machines called Objects have rendered conventional warfare and even tactical nuclear weapons seemingly obsolete. As a consequence of this military upheaval, all of the nations of the world have fractured into four coalitions which constantly wage war on each other; the "Legitimate Kingdom", focused on tradition; the "Capitalist Corporation" (in the anime the "Capitalist Enterprise"), which values profit; the "Information Alliance" (in the anime the "Intelligence Union"), focused on knowledge; and the "Faith Organization", which values religion above everything else. With the perception that only Objects can destroy Objects, modern warfare is reduced to duels between Objects, resulting in shorter, cleaner, and safer wars. However, this all changes when two regular soldiers from the Legitimate Kingdom, Qwenthur Barbotage and Havia Winchell, use their smarts and ingenuity to destroy the "Water Strider" Object of the Faith Organization all by themselves. Having proven that Objects created by man can also be destroyed by man, Qwenthur and Havia are thrown into a new world of harrowing adventures and dangerous [[Forlorn hope|suicide missions]], while together with Qwenthur befriending and saving the Legitimate Kingdom's Elite Melinda Brantini, of the Object the "Baby Magnum".

==Characters==

===Main characters===
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Heavy Object main characters.jpg|thumb|right|The three main characters of ''Heavy Object'' (from left to right):Havia Winchell, Milinda Brantini, and Qwenthur Barbotage with the Legitimate Kingdom's Heavy Object the "Baby Magnum"]] -->
;{{Nihongo|Qwenthur Barbotage|クウェンサー＝バーボタージュ|Kuwensā Bābotāju}}
:{{voiced by|[[Natsuki Hanae]]|[[Justin Briner]]<ref name="funi cast">{{cite web|url=https://www.funimation.com/blog/2015/11/07/fall-broadcast-dub-english-cast-announcement-heavy-object/|title=Fall Broadcast Dub English Cast Announcement – Heavy Object!|website=Funimation|date=November 7, 2015|accessdate=March 18, 2018}}</ref>}}
:Qwenthur, the main protagonist, is a young military cadet studying to be a Heavy Object engineer due to his fascination with Objects. His kindness and chivalry is only second to his quick wit. He is Havia's best friend and partner in their missions and usually acts as the brains of the duo. He is also close friends with Milinda after saving her from capture by the Faith Organization.

;{{Nihongo|Havia Winchell|ヘイヴィア＝ウィンチェル|Heivia Wincheru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kaito Ishikawa]]|[[Micah Solusod]]<ref name="funi cast"/>}}
:Havia is a member of the powerful Winchell family, and joins the military in the hopes of gaining enough fame and renown to earn his inheritance as the head of the Winchell family. He is Qwenthur's best friend and partner in their missions and typically handles all of the fighting. It is later revealed that he wishes to take control of the Winchell family in order to end its feud with the rival Vanderbilt family, so that he can marry his fiance who is part of the Vanderbilts.

;{{Nihongo|Milinda Brantini|ミリンダ＝ブランティーニ|Mirinda Burantīni}}
:{{voiced by|[[Eri Suzuki]]|[[Alexis Tipton]]<ref name="funi cast"/>}}
:Milinda is the pilot of the Legitimate Kingdom's Heavy Object "Baby Magnum", a first generation Object. After being saved by Qwenthur and Havia, Milinda quickly befriends the two soldiers and happily provides whatever support she can to their missions within Baby Magnum. It is also hinted that she has a crush on Qwenthur.

;{{Nihongo|Frolaytia Capistrano|フローレイティア＝カピストラーノ|Furōreitia Kapisutorāno}}
:{{voiced by|[[Shizuka Itō]]<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-10-13/shizuka-itou-joins-heavy-object-anime-cast/.79848|title = Shizuka Itou Joins ''Heavy Object'' Anime Cast|publisher = [[Anime News Network]]|date = October 13, 2014|accessdate = December 22, 2014}}</ref>|[[Morgan Garrett]]<ref name="funi cast"/>}}
:Frolaytia is Qwenthur and Havia's strict and heartless commanding officer. She's often happy to throw the pair into extremely dangerous missions and is quick to punish them for any disobedience. However, she secretly does care for Qwenthur and Havia and does whatever she can to make sure they complete their missions and survive. Her reason for joining the military is because she wants to avoid an arranged marriage with a long list of suitors who want to use her to produce a male heir offspring. Qwethur's actions help end the pressure of her 3rd suitor, Halreed Copacabana, who had just become 1st on the list.

===Legitimacy Kingdom===
;{{Nihongo|Ayami Cherryblossom|アヤミ＝チェリーブロッサム|Ayami Cherīburossamu}}
:{{voiced by|Mari Yokoo|[[Wendy Powell]]<ref name="funi cast"/>}}

;{{Nihongo|Flide|フライド|Furaido}}
