===Manga===
A [[manga]] adaptation with art by Shinsuke Inue was serialized in ASCII Media Works's [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazines ''[[Dengeki Black Maoh]]'' and ''[[Dengeki Maoh]]'' from 2009 to 2011. A single ''[[tankōbon]]'' of ''Heavy Object'' was released on May 27, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dengekibunko.dengeki.com/newreleases/978-4-04-870429-8/|script-title=ja:ヘヴィーオブジェクト|publisher=Dengeki Bunko|accessdate=March 22, 2015|language=Japanese}}</ref> A second manga adaptation, with art by Sakae Saitō and titled ''Heavy Object S'', was also serialized in ''Dengeki Maoh'' from 2011 to 2013. Three ''tankōbon'' volumes of the manga were released between August 27, 2012 and July 27, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dengekibunko.dengeki.com/newreleases/978-4-04-886818-1/|title=ヘヴィーオブジェクトS 01|publisher=Dengeki Bunko|accessdate=March 22, 2015|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dengekibunko.dengeki.com/newreleases/978-4-04-891803-9/|title=ヘヴィーオブジェクトS 03|publisher=Dengeki Bunko|accessdate=March 22, 2015|language=Japanese}}</ref> A third manga adaptation titled ''Heavy Object A'', also by Saitō, was serialized in ''Dengeki Maoh'' from 2015 to 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2015-02-08/heavy-object-novels-by-magical-index-kamachi-get-new-manga/.83697|title=''Heavy Object'' Novels by ''Magical Index''{{'}}s Kamachi Get New Manga|publisher=Anime News Network|date=February 8, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref> It also received three ''tankōbon'' volumes, released between February 27, 2015 and October 27, 2016.

===Anime===
{{see also|List of Heavy Object episodes}}
An [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[J.C.Staff]] was announced at the Dengeki Bunko Fall Festival event on October 5, 2014. Twenty-four episodes aired between October 2, 2015 and March 25, 2016, with the CG being handled by studio [[Sanzigen]].<ref name="Staff">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-03-15/heavy-object-anime-date-visual-staff-revealed/.85986|title=''Heavy Object'' Anime Date, Visual, Staff Revealed|publisher=Anime News Network|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref>

===Video games===
Several ''Heavy Object'' characters appeared in the sequel to ''[[Dengeki Bunko: Fighting Climax]]'', a fighting game by [[Sega]] featuring various characters from works published under the Dengeki Bunko imprint. Qwenthur is a playable character, assisted by Milinda and Havia, and Frolaytia is a support character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-06-08/heavy-object-characters-join-dengeki-bunko-fighting-climax-sequel/.89042|title=''Heavy Object'' Characters Join ''Dengeki Bunko Fighting Climax'' Sequel|publisher=Anime News Network|date=June 8, 2015|accessdate=June 10, 2015}}</ref>

